  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The hemolysis power-law model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger formulation) is applied under the theoretical precondition that erythrocyte damage accumulates linearly with exposure time and that shear stress–exposure time combinations are statistically independent and identically distributed (IID) across flow paths. Validation was performed at a single nominal operating point (4 L/min, 3000 RPM) where IID conditions are approximately satisfied; the broader COU spans five flow-speed combinations including off-design regimes where recirculation and secondary flows may invalidate the IID precondition.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
