    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. Validation at the nominal operating point demonstrates CFD model predicts NIH within 9% of bench measurement. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger model is the accepted regulatory standard for this device class. The credibility package supports the decision that CFD can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions across the five COU flow-speed combinations with Medium assurance, consistent with a Class II device at MRL 2. The relative hemolysis index criterion (RH < 1) is achievable with the demonstrated model fidelity.",
